Browser makers implemented headers first, so that is what people started recomending. 
When browser makers didn't implement scope people got laughed at for suggesting using it (understandable really) with the result that people who write sites got given the hard way first, and had to wait for the simple solution to be useful. 
Unfortunately (but again understanably really) users don't change their systems very often. 
So you don't get to take advantage of the newer features (well in terms of implementation - these were all proposed in '96 or '97) to make your life easier until users go through the process of upgrading, unless you are happy leaving a whole lot of users in the cold. 
